=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Prepare the oxindole branch by forming the 6-phenyl aryl framework (e.g., Suzuki coupling of a 6-halo isatin or corresponding 2-haloaniline-derived precursor with phenylboronic acid), then convert/reduce to 6-phenylindolin-2-one (6-phenyl-2-oxindole; optionally via 6-phenylisatin). | Step 2: Prepare the indole branch from a suitably halo-substituted indole and install the 3-diethylaminopropyl side chain with a protected 3-halopropyl-diethylamine equivalent, then deprotect if needed to give the 3-(3-diethylaminopropyl)-substituted indole. | Step 3: Subject that indole to Vilsmeier-Haack formylation to obtain 3-(3-diethylaminopropyl)-1H-indole-2-carbaldehyde. | Step 4: Condense 6-phenylindolin-2-one with 3-(3-diethylaminopropyl)-1H-indole-2-carbaldehyde under Knoevenagel conditions (e.g., piperidine/AcOH or NH4OAc) to install the exocyclic C=C bond. | Step 5: This final condensation furnishes the exact target, CCN(CC)CCCc1ccc2[nH]c(C=C3C(=O)Nc4cc(-c5ccccc5)ccc43)cc2c1.

